SIMPLE: fastigiated
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fastigiated
<hw>Fas*tig"i*a`ted</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>fastigium</ets> gable
end, top, height, summit.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Narrowing towards the
top.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Clustered, parallel, and upright,
as the branches of the Lombardy poplar; pointed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>United into a conical bundle, or
into a bundle with an enlarged head, like a sheaf of wheat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fastish</ent>⟦br⟧
